enrich student learning by bringing industry expertise and connections to the classroom. Professional Development Sponsorships Support student and/or faculty participation in industry and professional conferences (e.g., the National Retail Federation Big Show in New York or the National Restaurant Association show in Chicago). Graduate Student Fellowships Encourage graduate research through the sponsorship of named fellowships for advanced academic study or thesis research. Publication Sponsorships Endorse our School through the sponsorship of promotional pieces such as student newsletters, alumni updates, industry brochures, or other student recruitment materials. Industry Technology Fund Donate upgrades or emerging technologies for instructional use. Fund research for technology implementation. Named Scholarships Consider supporting one of our many named scholarships including the Jerry Dickenson, Lea Dopson, Ellen L. Flottman, Suzanne LaBrecque, Johnny Sue Reynolds, Bobye J. Riney, Florence I. Scoular, Richard Tas, or J.T. Whitaker scholarship. Â  To inquire about donations, please contact the College of Merchandising, Hospitality & Tourism at 940.565.2436 or email Dean Forney at jforney@unt.edu. Ways To Give Whether you are a graduate of theCollege of Merchandising, Hospitality & Tourism an industry partner, or a university friend, you can strengthen academic programs and invest in the future of our students through your generous donation. Listed below are the many ways you can give to our school and university. Giving to UNT Giving to the College of Merchandising, Hospitality & Tourism UNT Foundation Contact Us: College of Merchandising, Hospitality & Tourism 1155 Union Circle, #311100 Denton, TX 76203-5017 USA Voice: 940-565-2436 Fax: 940.565.4348 Visit Us: Chilton Hall Room Number: 331, 410 S. Avenue C Denton, TX 76201 http://cmht.unt.edu/ Email us: Have questions on content? Please contact us. cmht@unt.edu Technical problems: Have questions concerning how th